modules.description: Provides functions for storing and retrieving key/value pairs with support for persistent backends like PostgreSQL and SQLite. Operates on strings, integers, and serialized data structures for storage and retrieval. Used to manage user sessions and application state in web applications built with Eliom/Ocsigen.

Provides functions to parse and apply configuration settings for SQLite-backed sessions in Ocsigen Server, including database path, table names, and connection parameters. Works with configuration files in a structured XML format, extracting values for session management. Used to initialize persistent storage with custom settings during server setup.
